cfac <- function(x, breaks = NULL) {
    if (is.null(breaks))
        breaks <- unique(quantile(x, 0:10/10))
    x <- cut(x, breaks, include.lowest = TRUE, right = FALSE)
    levels(x) <- paste(breaks[-length(breaks)], ifelse(diff(breaks) >
        1, c(paste("-", breaks[-c(1, length(breaks))] - 1, sep = ""),
        "+"), ""), sep = "")
    return(x)
}

clog <- function(x) log(x + 0.5)

modelstat <- function(mod, dtf) {
    # Summaries
    mods1 <- summary(mod)
    mods2 <- summ(mod, confint = TRUE, digits = 3, ci.width = 0.95)

    # Attributes
    mods2atr <- attributes(mods2)

    # stat
    print(kable(cbind(na.omit(summary(mod)$coef), RR = na.omit(coef(mod)),
        na.omit(confint(mod)))))

    # Goodness of fit
    devresd <- round(residuals(mod, type = "deviance"), 3)
    devgof <- sum(devresd^2)

    pearson.resid <- round(resid(mod, type = "pearson"), 3)
    prsgof <- sum(pearson.resid^2)

    # Residual plots
    stddevres <- rstandard(mod)
    stdpearsons <- rstandard(mod, type = "pearson")

    # par(mfrow = c(2, 2)) plot(log(predict(mod)), devresd,
    # ylab = 'residuals') abline(h = 0)
    # plot(log(predict(mod)), stddevres, ylab =
    # 'Standardized residuals') abline(h = 0)
    # plot(log(predict(mod)), pearson.resid, ylab =
    # 'pearson residuals') abline(h = 0)
    # plot(log(predict(mod)), stdpearsons, ylab = 'pearson
    # Standardized residuals') abline(h = 0)

    # Predicted value plots expected <- round(predict(mod,
    # type = 'response'), 2) par(mfrow = c(1, 2))
    # plot(dtf$delivered, ylab = 'Actual') plot(expected,
    # ylab = 'Predicted')

    # plots
    par(mfrow = c(2, 2))
    # plot(log(fitted(mod)), (dtf$delivered -
    # fitted(mod))^2, xlab = expression(hat(mu)), ylab =
    # expression((y - hat(mu))^2)) abline(0, 1)
    plot(mod, which = c(1), main = "", caption = "")
    halfnorm(residuals(mod))
    # shapiro.qqnorm(residuals(mod, type = 'deviance'))
    plot(mod, which = c(2), main = "", caption = "")
    influencePlot(mod)

    # par(mfrow = c(2, 2)) plot(mod)

    # Step for model selection if(mods2atr$lmFamily$family
    # != 'quasipoisson'){ step(mod) }

    # poisson gof
    chiq <- pchisq(deviance(mod), df.residual(mod), lower = F)

    c(mods1$deviance, mods1$df.residual, chiq, mods2atr$rsqmc,
        mods2atr$aic, mods2atr$bic, devgof, prsgof)
}
